Installation dependencies outside of emacs:

- pyinotify (sudo pip install pyinotify)
- PybTex (sudo pip install pybtex)
- pyperclip (sudo pip install pyperclip)
- Tkinter (should be installed with Python)
- pdfgrep (sudo apt-get install pdfgrep)
- Graph::Easy (sudo apt-get install libgraph-easy-perl)

- sudo pip install -U selenium
- sudo apt install npm
- sudo apt install nodejs-legacy
- npm install phantomjs-prebuilt
  The path to phantomjs executable will be printed. Copy this executable to /usr/bin/ or /usr/local/bin/ so it should be in the PATH

Optional: Link Klipper for Chrome

Emacs packages:

- org
- org-ref
- pdf-tools (after installing the package from the package manager, need to run pdf-tools-install).
- smooth-scrolling